The tailwind.config.js file is responsible for customizing and configuring various aspects of the Tailwind CSS framework.
It allows you to modify default settings, extend or override existing configurations, add custom styles, and enable 
or disable specific features.

npm install next-auth == by using developer.spotify.com => spotify_client id, spotify_client secret
NextAuth.js simplifies the implementation of authentication in Next.js applications by providing a unified API and pre-built integrations with popular authentication providers.

npm i node-fetch
Node-fetch is a popular JavaScript library used for making HTTP requests in Node.js environments. It is 
a light-weight module that provides a fetch-like API for making HTTP requests to external resources such as APIs, web services, or other servers.

JWT Callback
This callback is called whenever a JSON Web Token is created (i.e. at sign in) or updated (i.e whenever a 
session is accessed in the client). The returned value will be encrypted, and it is stored in a cookie.

